title: Eighteenth Century Painting (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Funk & Wagnalls | Pdf | Eng | 1972 | 207 p | 27 MB

European culture of the eighteenth century may be said to have possessed a character of unity transcending national divisions, but it was also extremely complex.

The changes in society during this time explain all the contrasts of an era that embraced equally happily the serious and the frivolous, the real and the imaginary, in a vast liberation of senses and spirit. In EIGHTEENTH CENTURY PAINTING, Clair Gay surveys this variety of European art and relates its development to the important social, cultural, and political upheavals that influenced it
